    • isStabilizable

      public static boolean isStabilizable​(int states, int inputs, double[] A, double[] B)
      Returns true if (A, B) is a stabilizable pair.

      (A,B) is stabilizable if and only if the uncontrollable eigenvalues of A, if any, have absolute values less than one, where an eigenvalue is uncontrollable if rank(lambda * I - A, B) < n where n is number of states.

      Parameters:
      states - the number of states of the system.
      inputs - the number of inputs to the system.
      A - System matrix.
      B - Input matrix.
      Returns:
      If the system is stabilizable.
